## Architecture: Direct Rendering (No Iframe)

Components render directly in the React tree. The canvas uses a `data-builder-page-frame` wrapper at a fixed `zoom` scale. Overlay positions are computed via `getBoundingClientRect()` against the page frame.

**Key DOM attributes:**
- `data-builder-id` — injected via ref callback on every SDUI node; used for hit-testing, selection, overlay positioning
- `data-builder-type` — node type string
- `data-builder-page-frame` — marks the canvas viewport
- `data-builder-overlay` — marks overlay elements (excluded from selection hit-testing)
- `data-builder-hidden` — nodes marked hidden

**`builderMode`**: a flag passed to the SDUI renderer that disables action execution and enables builder-specific ref callbacks.

---

## Design Panel Sections (Right Panel)

Full section list in render order:

0. **Content** *(Text/Heading/ButtonText + Button)* — Textarea to edit `node.text` directly. For Button, edits the first `ButtonText` child. Shown before Position & Size.
1. **Position & Size** — X/Y (read-only DOM metrics), W/H (inline `style.width/height` + `minWidth/minHeight: 0`)
2. **Dimensions** — W mode: Hug (`w-fit`) / Fill (`w-full`) / Fixed (removes fit/full). H mode: same with `h-*`. Also: Min W / Max W / Min H / Max H (inline `style.minWidth/maxWidth/minHeight/maxHeight`).
3. **Self Alignment** — How this node aligns inside its parent flex container: `self-auto/start/center/end/stretch/baseline`
4. **Transform** — Rotation (inline `style.transform = rotate(Ndeg)`), Flip H (`-scale-x-100`), Flip V (`-scale-y-100`)
5. **Alignment** *(containers only)* — 9-cell grid (items-* + justify-*). Only shown for Box/VStack/HStack/Pressable.
6. **Auto Layout** *(containers only)* — Flex direction, wrap, gap (inline `style.gap`), space-between mode
7. **Padding** — Exact pixel values via inline `style.paddingLeft/Right/Top/Bottom`. Combined H/V or individual toggle.
8. **Margin** — Exact pixel values via inline `style.marginLeft/Right/Top/Bottom`. Combined H/V or individual toggle.
9. **Display & Interaction** — Display type (`block/flex/grid/hidden`), Cursor (`cursor-pointer` etc.)
10. **Clip content** — Toggle `overflow-hidden`
11. **Fill** — Background color (inline `style.backgroundColor`, initialized from computed DOM color) + bg-opacity slider
12. **Stroke** — Border color (inline `style.borderColor`, initialized from computed DOM color), border width, border style
13. **Effects** — Drop shadow (`shadow-*` class)
14. **Typography** *(Text/Heading/ButtonText only)* — Size, Weight, Leading, Tracking, Text alignment, Decoration, Transform, Text color (inline `style.color`, initialized from computed DOM color)
15. **Border Radius** — 4-corner selects. All equal → single global token. Mixed → per-corner tokens.
16. **Opacity** — Inline `style.opacity` (0–1). Slider min=5.
17. **Selection colors** — Hex swatches from className
18. **Layout Guide** — Grid overlay toggle

